dough.Setup(d => d.RollOut()).Returns(true);

var toppings = new Mock<Toppings>();
toppings.Setup(t => t.Apply()).Returns("Cheese");

var pizza = new Pizza(dough.Object, toppings.Object);
```

This way, you can test your Pizza class without worrying about the details of the Dough or Toppings classes.

